courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students should be able to:
1. Understand the roles of social entrepreneurship in society, and the challenges and opportunities of social innovation;
2. Formulate innovative ways to identify and address social problems;
3. Design appropriate and accountable measures to evaluate social impacts;
4. Apply tools and frameworks for launching and managing social entrepreneurship;
5. Evaluate different financial and strategic options for social entrepreneurship.

Upon completion of this course, students should be able to:
1. Deliver innovative and feasible solutions in a real entrepreneurial context;
2. Accumulate hands-on working experience under guidance of practitioners;
3. Derive understanding of entrepreneurship-related knowledge and transform it through real entrepreneurship experience;
4. Develop analytical and problem-solving skills in a team with classmates and/or practitioners.

Upon completion of this course, students should be able to:
1. Acquire an in-depth understanding in one or more specific sectors in entrepreneurship;
2. Appreciate and evaluate the best practices, opportunities, and challenges in different contexts of entrepreneurship;
3. Employ tools and knowledge in entrepreneurship in analyzing real cases and generating solutions;
4. Develop problem-solving and communication skills by delivering convincing solutions.

