After completing this course, students should be able to:
(1) understand HRM issues and practices which affect organizational performance;
(2) develop a strategic approach for managing human resources.

After completing this course, students should be able to:
(1) explain conceptual frameworks for analysing the complexity of management decision making;
(2) develop a holistic mind-set to study management decision making as an interaction of self, others and context;
(3) apply conceptual frameworks, effective decision-making skills and tactics to diagnose the practical management problems in the workplace and come up with proper solutions to deal with these problems; and
(4) create an environment in which students can enhance self-awareness and self-reflection, synthesize new ideas, and develop their personal strengths and decision-making abilities.

Students will be able to understand:
